Poliovirus Weekly Update as of 20 Apr 2022, World Health Organization
---------------------------------------------------------------------
New wild poliovirus isolates reported this week:
AFP cases: 0
Environment: 0
Others: 0

New cVDPV isolates reported this week:
AFP cases: 41
Environment: 0
Others: 16

Summary of new polioviruses this week:
- DR Congo: 6 cVDPV2 cases
- Nigeria: 1 cVDPV2 case
- Yemen: 34 cVDPV2 cases

Afghanistan
• No new WPV1 or cVDPV2 viruses were reported this week. There is 1 WPV1 case reported in 2022 and 4 in 2021. The total number of cVDPV2 cases remains 43.

Pakistan
• No new WPV1 or cVDPV2 viruses were reported this week. The total number of WPV1 cases in 2021 remains 1. The total number of cVDPV2 cases remains 8.

Benin
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 3 cases reported in 2021.

Burkina Faso
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 2 cases reported in 2021.

Cameroon
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 3 cases reported in 2021.

Central African Republic
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are no cases reported in 2021.

Chad
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are no cases reported in 2021.

Congo (Republic of)
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 2 cases reported in 2021.

Côte d'Ivoire
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are no reported cases in 2021.

Djibouti
• No cVDPV2 positive environmental samples were reported this week. There are 5 positive environmental samples reported in the country, linked to the virus circulating in Yemen.

Democratic Republic of the Congo (DR Congo)
• 6 cases of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) were reported; 5 in Maniema and 1 in Nord Kivu bringing the number of 2022 cases to 22. There are 28 cases from 2021.

Egypt
• No cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported. There are 14 positive samples reported in the country.
• An internal surveillance review is scheduled for May [2022], as part of preparations for the expected Outbreak Response Assessment.

Ethiopia
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 10 cases reported in 2021.

Gambia
• No cVDPV2 positive environmental samples were reported this week. There are 9 positive samples reported in 2021.

Guinea
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 6 cases in 2021.

Guinea-Bissau
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 3 cases in the country which are linked to the Jigawa outbreak in Nigeria in 2021.

Israel
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 3 (cVDPV3) was reported this week. There is 1 case reported in the country in 2022.

Liberia
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 3 cVDPV2 cases in the country in 2021.

Madagascar
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 1 (cVDPV1) was reported this week. The number of 2021 cases remains 13. There is 1 case in 2022.

Malawi
• No case of WPV1 was reported this week. In February [2022], the country reported the 1st WPV1 case on the continent since 2016, with onset of paralysis in November 2021.
• Following the 1st of a series of multi-country outbreak response implemented in March [2022], preparations are ongoing in both Malawi and neighbouring countries for the subsequent campaigns.
• In total, at least 4, multi-country campaigns will be implemented.
• For upcoming campaigns, lessons learned from the 1st round will be reviewed, and corrective measures implemented as needed for subsequent rounds.

Mauritania
• No cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported this week. There are 7 positive samples linked to the Jigawa outbreak in 2021.
• The second round of nOPV2 campaigns was held in the country from [29 Mar to 2 Apr 2022]. Preparations for the campaign had focused on planning and coordination, training, monitoring and supervision, vaccine logistics and cold chain, advocacy and social mobilization and microplanning.
• More than 2500 supervisors to vaccination teams had been mobilized and recruited across the country to support the activity.
• High coverage was reported, with more than 870 000 children reached and vaccinated.
• A full analysis of the activity is underway, and lessons learned will help inform planning and implementation of future campaigns.

Mozambique
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 2 cases reported in 2021.
• In response to the confirmed cVDPV2 outbreak in the country, the Minister of Health declared the outbreak to be a national public health emergency in February [2022].
• Outbreak response will be implemented, through high-quality SIAs covering the infected provinces. A national emergency operations centre has been established to coordinate outbreak response activities.
• Mozambique is also participating in multi-country, subregional emergency outbreak response with Malawi and other countries, in response to the recent detection of WPV1 in Malawi.

Niger
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 17 cases reported in 2021.

Nigeria
• 1 case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported in Katsina bringing the number of 2022 cases to 16. The number of 2021 cases remains 415.

Senegal
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 17 cases reported in 2021.

Sierra Leone
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 5 cases reported in 2021.

Somalia
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There is 1 case reported in 2022 and 1 case in 2021.

South Sudan
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 9 cVDPV2 cases reported in 2021.

Tajikistan
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 32 cases reported in 2021.

Uganda
• No cVDPV2 positive environmental sample was reported this week. There are 2 positive samples linked to the N'Djamena outbreak in Chad reported in 2021.

Ukraine
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There are 2 cases reported in 2021.

Yemen
• 34 cases of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) were reported this week; Abyan (4), Albaidah (2), Alhudaidah (4), Aljawf (6), Almahaweet (1), Amran (2), Hadramoat Sayeun (1), Lahaj (5), Marib (1), Saadah (5) and Taiz (3). The number of cVDPV2 cases now stands at 5 in 2022 and 61 in 2021. There are also 3 cVDPV1 cases in 2021.

Zambia
• In response to the Malawi WPV1 polio outbreak declared on 17 Feb 2022, synchronized polio vaccination campaigns are planned from [25 Apr 2022] in 10 provinces where a total of 4 072 391 children aged 0-5 years are targeted.
• An advocacy meeting with the Minister of Health (MOH), permanent secretary and Partners was held on [14 Apr 2022].
• Distribution of bOPV vaccine and supplies to districts has begun.

Officially reported WPV1 and cVDPV cases as of [19 Apr 2022]
Wild poliovirus (WPV)
- Total global WPV1 cases in 2022: 1 (compared with 2 for the same period in 2021)
- Total global WPV1 cases in 2021: 6

Circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus (cVDPV) cases
- Total global cVDPV cases in 2022: 46 (compared with 60 for the same period in 2021)
- Total global cVDPV cases in 2021: 688

--
Communicated by:
ProMED

[This week's report has 3 countries reporting AFP cases associated with cVDPV2 -- DR Congo, Nigeria and Yemen with Yemen reporting 34 cases all with onset in 2021.

A map showing the locations of each confirmed case of polio worldwide in the past 12 months can be found at https://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/. One can see cases of cVDPV in a band across Africa and in Israel, Ukraine, Tajikistan, Afghanistan and Pakistan, cVDPV1 in Madagascar and Yemen, and WPV1 in Afghanistan and Pakistan. - Mod.MPP]

