Summary of new polioviruses this week:
- Israel: 4 cVDPV3 positive environmental samples
- Nigeria: 1 cVDPV2 case and 4 positive environmental samples

Israel
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 3 (cVDPV3) was reported this week. There is 1 case reported in the country in 2022.
• 4 cVDPV3 positive environmental samples were reported in Jerusalem.

Nigeria
• 1 case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported in Niger province bringing the number of 2022 cases to 15. The number of 2021 cases remains 415.
• 4 positive environmental samples were reported; 2 in Bauchi, and 1 each in Kano and Katsina.

