Nigeria
• 6 cases of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) were reported; 1 each in Bauchi, Kaduna, Sokoto and Zamfara and 2 in Kebbi. The number of 2022 cases now stands at 14. The number of 2021 cases remains 415.
• 7 positive environmental samples were reported; 2 each in Borno and Gombe and 3 in Kano.

